		<h1 class="h3">Typography</h1>
		<hr>
		<p>GatherContent uses Whitney from the folk over at <a href="http://typography.com">typography.com</a> across the marketing site and application.</p>
		<p>We don't style heading tags (<code>h1, h2, h3</code>, etc). We use classes to style headings as this makes more sense in the context of our web application due to the separation of document semantics from style.</p>
		<h2 class="h4">Headings</h2>
		<h1 class="page__headline">Page headline</h1>
		<p><code>.page__headline</code> <code>24px</code></p>
		<hr>
		<h1 class="content__headline">Content headline</h1>
		<p><code>.content__headline</code> <code>20px</code></p>
		<hr>
		<h1 class="fl-1">First-level heading</h1>
		<p><code>.fl-1</code> <code>18px</code></p>
		<hr>
		<h1 class="fl-2">Second-level heading</h1>
		<p><code>.fl-2</code> <code>16px</code></p>
		<hr>
		<h1 class="fl-3">Third-level heading</h1>
		<p><code>.fl-3</code> <code>14px</code></p>
		<hr>
